00:00:06:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:06:200000.Dialogue: This is the worst cobbler I've ever eaten. It tastes like it's made of actual ground-up shoemaker.

00:00:13:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:13:100000.Dialogue: Amusing. A play on the two meanings of "cobbler."

00:00:19:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:19:170000.Dialogue: Hey, guys. Guess who I found at LAX? My baby sister Priya.

00:00:23:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:23:130000.Dialogue: Excuse me, I object. You propose a guessing game, yet you don't give me enough time to guess. For the record, I was going to say: Your sister Priya.

00:00:33:190000.Speaker: Priya
00:00:33:190000.Dialogue: Oh, Sheldon. You haven't changed a bit, have you?

00:00:39:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:39:110000.Dialogue: The hope has been that you'd eventually bend to public opinion. So, Priya, what brings you back to L.A.?

00:00:45:200000.Speaker: Priya
00:00:45:200000.Dialogue: I have a one-day layover on my way to Toronto. Corporate merger.

00:00:49:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:49:090000.Dialogue: Can you believe it? Little Priya's one of the lead attorneys for the biggest car company in India.

00:00:53:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:53:070000.Dialogue: Given that when we met her, she was finishing law school and planning an internship at a large Indian car company, it's actually extremely plausible.

00:01:01:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:01:140000.Dialogue: And your poll numbers just keep dropping.

00:01:05:200000.Speaker: Priya
00:01:05:200000.Dialogue: I want to catch up with all of you, but first I really must visit the loo.

00:01:09:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:09:020000.Dialogue: I'm going, too; I'll show you where it is.

00:01:12:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:12:020000.Dialogue: All right, this goes without saying, but I'm just going to say it anyway. Hands off my sister.

00:01:17:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:17:120000.Dialogue: Why would I touch her? She's covered with airplane germs.

00:01:21:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:21:080000.Dialogue: I'm so not talking to you. I'm talking to him.

00:01:24:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:24:230000.Dialogue: Hey. I've got a girlfriend now. Oh, please.

00:01:31:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:31:180000.Dialogue: Let's just agree they're both hot.

00:01:33:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:33:120000.Dialogue: But dude, that's my sister you're talking about!

00:01:36:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:36:210000.Dialogue: Okay, forget who's hotter. The first time Priya came to L.A., Leonard and I made a pact out of respect to our friendship and to you that neither of us would hit on her.

00:01:59:120000.Speaker: Priya
00:01:59:120000.Dialogue: It's really nice to see you again, Leonard.

00:02:01:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:01:200000.Dialogue: Yeah. It's good to see you, too. Here you go.

00:02:39:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:39:110000.Dialogue: So you got any special plans with your sister?

00:02:42:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:42:010000.Dialogue: Oh, not really. Just hang out.

00:02:44:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:44:100000.Dialogue: I always tell people, "If you have only one day in Los Angeles, make it a train day."

00:02:52:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:52:110000.Dialogue: The fun starts with brunch at Carney's in Studio City, a hotdog stand in a converted railroad dining car. Next stop, Travel Town, an outdoor museum featuring 43 railroad engines, cars, and other rolling stock from the 1880s to the 1930s. And, finally, we're off to the glitz and glamour of Hollywood, for dinner at--that's right-- the Hollywood Carney's, a hotdog stand in a different converted railroad dining car.

00:03:20:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:20:180000.Dialogue: I don't think we're going to do that.

00:03:23:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:23:210000.Dialogue: Well, then apparently you hate fun.

00:03:31:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:31:150000.Dialogue: Priya's not back yet? Well, I guess that's not unusual. Women, men, the whole sitting-standing deal. So what are we talking about?

00:03:42:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:42:170000.Dialogue: Did you make it clear that it's two different train cars turned into hotdog stands?

00:03:48:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:48:210000.Dialogue: I guess he just hates fun.

00:03:56:170000.Speaker: Priya
00:03:56:170000.Dialogue: Okay, so... what's new with you guys?

00:04:01:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:01:200000.Dialogue: Yeah, I just want to put it out there in case I inadvertently squirt any pheromones in your direction.

00:04:11:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:11:110000.Dialogue: So, Priya, what are your plans while you're here?

00:04:13:220000.Speaker: Priya
00:04:13:220000.Dialogue: I don't know. I just have the one day.

00:04:23:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:23:130000.Dialogue: You might as well just wait at the airport for your flight.

00:04:28:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:28:220000.Dialogue: "You are in a forest. "There is quicksand to the west, a path leads to the east." (typing) Go east. An iron gate blocks your way. (typing) Open gate. It's locked. Hmm. Well, so much for that.

00:04:55:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:55:010000.Dialogue: It's getting pretty late. How come you're still up?

00:04:56:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:56:210000.Dialogue: I found an emulator online that lets you play classic text-based computer games from the 1980s.

00:05:04:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:04:200000.Dialogue: Oh, yes. It runs on the world's most powerful graphics chip: imagination.

00:05:10:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:10:120000.Dialogue: You've really got to get out more.

00:05:15:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:15:050000.Dialogue: (typing) Go north. You can't go that way. (typing) Go west. A troll blocks your passage. Okay. Fasten your seatbelts.

00:05:27:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:27:090000.Dialogue: (typing) Kill troll. With what? (typing) With sword. (knock at door) You don't have the sword. Good golly, it's as if it's actually happening to me.

00:05:47:230000.Speaker: Priya
00:05:47:230000.Dialogue: You said he goes to bed at 9:00.

00:05:49:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:49:180000.Dialogue: Yeah, he does, but he got caught up in a computer game and...

00:05:52:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:52:110000.Dialogue: (typing) SHELDON: Hit troll with axe! (typing) Hit troll with axe! Hit troll with axe! My, this is one tough troll.

00:06:03:150000.Speaker: Priya
00:06:03:150000.Dialogue: Can't you get rid of him?

00:06:05:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:05:070000.Dialogue: If the past is any indication, no.

00:06:08:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:08:020000.Dialogue: SHELDON: Leonard, I'm trapped in quicksand! The axe is dragging me down!

00:06:23:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:23:130000.Dialogue: Hold on. Trying to figure out how to get the bucket, so I can carry the mud past the dragon.

00:06:29:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:29:010000.Dialogue: Sheldon, you need to work in the morning.

00:06:35:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:35:170000.Dialogue: Really? You're going to risk getting sleepy in the middle of your thermodynamic fluctuations seminar? You know what happens when you yawn in public.

00:06:46:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:46:180000.Dialogue: Everyone will see my oddly shaped uvula.

00:06:51:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:51:230000.Dialogue: You don't want that, do you?

00:06:54:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:54:080000.Dialogue: No. But it's a shame our society mocks the differently uvulated.

00:07:04:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:04:020000.Dialogue: Uh, building manager. They have to fix a pipe, so the water'll be off tomorrow from noon to 2:00.

00:07:10:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:10:150000.Dialogue: That's unacceptable. We're supposed to be given written notice.

00:07:13:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:13:140000.Dialogue: Well, no, it doesn't matter-- we'll be at work.

00:07:15:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:15:090000.Dialogue: What if I spill tomato soup on my shirt, and have to come home to change, only to find there's no water for an enzyme soak?

00:07:24:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:24:030000.Dialogue: I'll have the chicken noodle. Good night!

00:07:31:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:31:060000.Dialogue: (whispering): We're going to have to be very quiet.

00:07:38:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:38:040000.Dialogue: SHELDON: I know how to get the bucket! I can turn the axe around and use the handle to reach it. Let's see. (typing) Go north. You are in a forest. (typing) Go north. You are in a forest. (typing) Go north. You are in a forest. Oh dear, I believe I'm lost. Well, I'll just have to get a fresh start tomorrow.

00:08:00:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:00:020000.Dialogue: No, no, no! You just took a wrong turn. You just need to map it out. Come on, I'll help you. So you stopped at the stream, and you turned north three times?

00:08:08:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:08:190000.Dialogue: You're right. You're lost. Good luck.

00:08:21:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:21:140000.Dialogue: I don't know. When I'm in bed with a girl, it's just-- it's my go-to response.

00:08:25:220000.Speaker: Priya
00:08:25:220000.Dialogue: It's 6:00. I have to get back to Raj's before he wakes up and realizes I'm gone.

00:08:29:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:29:180000.Dialogue: Oh. Right. Sure. I wish you could stay in L.A. a while longer.

00:08:35:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:35:150000.Dialogue: You know, I was thinking: There are some great research facilities in India.

00:08:40:020000.Speaker: Priya
00:08:40:020000.Dialogue: Where are you going with this, Leonard?

00:08:42:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:42:210000.Dialogue: Well, I'm just saying, you know, I don't have any real ties here, so if I were to move to New Delhi, we could, you know-- go out.

00:08:52:170000.Speaker: Priya
00:08:52:170000.Dialogue: Leonard, didn't we have this conversation five years ago?

00:08:56:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:56:090000.Dialogue: Well, yes, but... things have changed. You know, you're older, I'm older-- Look, no more superhero bed sheets.

00:09:02:090000.Speaker: Priya
00:09:02:090000.Dialogue: Sweetheart, just because we have fun when I come to town doesn't mean I want to have a serious relationship.

00:09:10:100000.Speaker: Priya
00:09:10:100000.Dialogue: Mm-mm. And besides, I could never bring a white boy home to my parents. They'd have a cow. Which is a much bigger deal in India.

00:09:19:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:19:190000.Dialogue: I'm not that white. My great-great-grandmother was half Cherokee. I know that's not the right kind of Indian, but it is something.

00:09:36:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:36:130000.Dialogue: Oh, uh, yeah. I was trying to see if I could laugh as a woman.

00:09:42:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:42:220000.Dialogue: Oh! Well, good job. Quite convincing.

00:09:49:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:49:030000.Dialogue: And is that lipstick on your cheek and neck?

00:09:54:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:54:010000.Dialogue: My sympathies. I'm no stranger to the crimson scourge that is dermatitis. Can I interest you in a topical steroid from my lotion and unguent collection?

00:10:05:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:05:020000.Dialogue: Uh, yeah, yeah, that sounds great.

00:10:08:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:08:020000.Dialogue: Very well. I'm sure I can find something that will help you ditch that itch.

00:10:13:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:13:180000.Dialogue: Okay, he's in the bathroom. Let's go.

00:10:19:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:19:040000.Dialogue: Do you prefer ointment or cream?

00:10:25:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:25:050000.Dialogue: With or without a numbing agent?

00:10:27:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:27:130000.Dialogue: Really, Leonard? There are no heroes when it comes to dermatitis.

00:10:36:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:36:230000.Dialogue: Well, I think I have a nice 2009 AnaMantle HC. It's usually indicated for acutely inflamed hemorrhoids, but it also goes nicely with non-mucosal body parts.

00:10:54:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:54:220000.Dialogue: (whispering): Okay, hurry, hurry, hurry. Come on, come on, come on.

00:11:06:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:06:080000.Dialogue: For shame, Leonard, for shame. And to think, I was ready to waste the last of my good hemorrhoid cream on you.

00:11:27:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:27:040000.Dialogue: Is that really what you want to talk about, Leonard?

00:11:32:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:32:010000.Dialogue: What do you want to talk about?

00:11:33:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:33:110000.Dialogue: Please don't tell anyone I spent the night with Raj's sister.

00:11:40:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:40:230000.Dialogue: No one's going to ask if I spent the night with Raj's sister.

00:11:43:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:43:130000.Dialogue: Perhaps, but they might ask me something else.

00:11:53:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:53:120000.Dialogue: Priya and I are both adults. I didn't betray Raj.

00:11:57:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:57:090000.Dialogue: In fact, you did, but I was referring to Howard.

00:12:02:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:02:000000.Dialogue: April 12, 2005. Bob's Big Boy, Toluca Lake. Raj had just introduced us to Priya for the first time. She was enjoying the sweet taste of Hindu rebellion in the form of a Bob's Super Big Boy hamburger. In order to preserve your friendship, you and Howard made a pinky swear that neither of you would attempt to woo her. (sighs) I had a patty melt.

00:12:32:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:32:190000.Dialogue: Violation of the Roommate Agreement's overnight guest notification clause.

00:12:36:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:36:190000.Dialogue: Okay, fine, I-I'm a horrible human being. I'm the Darth Vader of Pasadena.

00:12:41:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:41:190000.Dialogue: You're far too short to be Darth Vader.

00:12:45:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:45:100000.Dialogue: At best you might be a turncoat Ewok.

00:12:48:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:48:080000.Dialogue: My point is: Priya's gone and it would be much better if no one else found out about us.

00:12:55:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:55:060000.Dialogue: You mean you want me to keep a secret?

00:12:58:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:58:080000.Dialogue: You know I can't keep a secret.

00:12:59:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:59:230000.Dialogue: You can if you try. Think about it this way: um, if I were Batman and you were Alfred, you'd keep that secret, right?

00:13:07:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:07:030000.Dialogue: Why do you get to be Batman?

00:13:35:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:35:200000.Dialogue: I know, that's why I shortened it.

00:13:40:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:40:170000.Dialogue: I came to go over your alibi for last night.

00:13:45:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:45:200000.Dialogue: You've asked me to lie on your behalf, and as you know, I am deeply uncomfortable with impromptu dishonesty, so I've provided you with an ironclad alibi. You couldn't have spent last night with Priya because you were with another woman.

00:14:00:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:00:050000.Dialogue: Oh, I'm so sure I'm gonna regret this, but who was I with?

00:14:05:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:05:130000.Dialogue: The fun-loving and morally loose Miss Maggie McGarry.

00:14:11:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:11:020000.Dialogue: You met her at Pasadena's most popular Irish watering hole, Lucky Baldwin's, where Maggie spends her nights tending bar with a head full of curls and a heart full of dreams.

00:14:20:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:20:190000.Dialogue: Leonard, call me if you are interested in coitus. Sincerely, Maggie McGarry." "Leonard, call me if you are interested in coitus.

00:14:28:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:28:130000.Dialogue: And if anyone were to actually call that number, they will hear this.

00:14:34:180000.Speaker: Mechanical voice on Sheldon’s phone
00:14:34:180000.Dialogue: FEMALE TEXT-TO-SPEECH VOICE: Top of the morning to you. You've reached Maggie McGarry.

00:14:40:050000.Speaker: Mechanical voice on Sheldon’s phone
00:14:40:050000.Dialogue: Leave a message after the wee little beep.

00:14:45:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:45:110000.Dialogue: It's pretty convincing, huh? That wasn't even a real person. And here is the clincher: a lock of Maggie's flaming auburn hair.

00:14:57:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:57:060000.Dialogue: From an orangutan in the primate lab.

00:15:01:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:01:040000.Dialogue: Well, no one's going to run a DNA test on it, Leonard. Honestly, you overthink everything.

00:15:06:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:06:080000.Dialogue: Sheldon, I don't need an alibi. Nobody's going to ask about last night as long as you just zip your lip. Thank you. Now, don't worry, everything is going to be fine.

00:15:35:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:35:160000.Dialogue: Hey, Leonard, will you please tell Howard my sister has never been attracted to him?

00:15:39:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:39:180000.Dialogue: Come on, Raj, how am I supposed to know who she is attracted to or was attracted to or who she might be attracted to in the future?

00:15:50:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:50:070000.Dialogue: And I have nothing to contribute to this conversation.

00:15:56:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:56:190000.Dialogue: Because I, too, know absolutely nothing about Priya's preferences in male companionship.

00:16:02:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:02:170000.Dialogue: And with that, I will re-zip my lip.

00:16:06:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:06:050000.Dialogue: Hey, so what did you guys think of the new episode of Caprica last night?

00:16:11:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:11:140000.Dialogue: Didn't see it? (chuckles) What were you doing?

00:16:20:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:20:210000.Dialogue: Yeah, I, uh, went for a drink.

00:16:23:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:23:040000.Dialogue: Really, you? Where, w-where'd you go?

00:16:37:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:37:080000.Dialogue: Oh, I've heard of that place. Isn't that Pasadena's favorite Irish watering hole?

00:16:46:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:46:180000.Dialogue: Did you meet anyone interesting there, perhaps a promiscuous, redheaded barmaid?

00:16:53:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:53:130000.Dialogue: As a matter of fact... I-I-I-I-I can't, I can't, I can't do it.

00:16:56:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:56:230000.Dialogue: Sure you can, you're doing fine, it's very believable.

00:17:00:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:00:120000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, Raj, but the truth is, I was with Priya last night.

00:17:04:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:04:220000.Dialogue: Don't listen to him. He's still light-headed from all the Irish whiskey and pickled eggs in his system.

00:17:09:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:09:180000.Dialogue: What were you doing with Priya?

00:17:11:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:11:160000.Dialogue: I believe they engaged in coitus, but more importantly, if Leonard had not abandoned his story, would you have found it plausible?

00:17:21:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:21:050000.Dialogue: How could you? We had a pact.

00:17:23:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:23:100000.Dialogue: Excuse me, I think How could you? She's my sister takes precedence over a five-year-old pinky swear.

00:17:28:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:28:100000.Dialogue: May I point out, in a parallel universe, your friends are saying Maggie McGarry-- she sounds lovely.

00:17:34:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:34:180000.Dialogue: Look, I-I admit it, I may have crossed a line here, but come on, Raj, your sister is a grown woman, and to her, I'm a forbidden piece of white chocolate.

00:17:44:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:17:44:160000.Dialogue: KOOTHRAPPALI: I don't believe it. This is a terrible betrayal of my trust.

00:17:48:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:48:040000.Dialogue: No, w-w-would it help if I told you that I offered her my heart, and she kind of stomped on it?

00:18:03:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:03:180000.Dialogue: Well, Raj, I just want to say that I'd never betray your trust. Unlike Leonard, I respect you.

00:18:15:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:15:130000.Dialogue: Was it out of respect that you didn't tell Raj about the time you dropped his iPhone in a urinal?

00:18:21:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:21:050000.Dialogue: Dude, I put that thing on my face!

00:18:24:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:24:120000.Dialogue: I think a more amusing violation of Raj's trust is when Howard convinced him that foreigners give presents to Americans on Thanksgiving.

00:18:33:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:33:190000.Dialogue: Hey, I didn't see you giving back your Snoopy snow cone maker.

00:18:38:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:38:040000.Dialogue: That was all a lie? This year's gifts are already wrapped.

00:18:41:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:18:41:100000.Dialogue: And as long as we're talking about betraying our friends, how about the month Sheldon spent grinding up insects and mixing them into Leonard's food?

00:18:48:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:48:090000.Dialogue: SHELDON: Well, excuse me. That was not a betrayal. That was an experiment to determine at what concentration food starts tasting "mothy."

00:18:57:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:57:160000.Dialogue: You put moths in my food?! For science.

00:19:04:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:19:04:170000.Dialogue: I can't believe you kissed my sister with moth mouth.

00:19:07:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:07:050000.Dialogue: Well, I can't believe you used Sheldon's toothbrush.

00:19:13:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:19:13:160000.Dialogue: Not the brush part, just the little rubber thing to pick food from my teeth and massage my gums.

00:19:26:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:26:010000.Dialogue: Okay, I-I think it's safe to say that we've all done some things we're not particularly proud of. But come on, we're friends. Friends overlook each other's minor lapses. For the record, Howard, I'm sorry that I broke our pact.

00:19:42:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:42:120000.Dialogue: Thank you. And I'm sorry about your phone and Thanksgiving. And while we're at it, you don't have to wash our clothes on the Fourth of July.

00:19:54:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:19:54:180000.Dialogue: As long as we're apologizing, Sheldon, I'm, I'm sorry I used your toothbrush.

00:20:00:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:00:020000.Dialogue: And I'm sorry... but that behavior is beyond the pale and cannot be tolerated. We are no longer friends.

00:20:07:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:20:07:150000.Dialogue: I got you a talking Thomas the Tank Engine for Thanksgiving.

00:20:20:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is making snowcones.
00:20:20:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
